Suppose you bought a domain and you want to host it from aws so these are the steps to be followed

---------
Step : 01
---------

aws > route53 > dashboard > create hosted zone > add your domain name in it and then click on create hosted zone

---------
Step : 02
---------

now go to go daddy and in manage domain > DNS > add your hosted zones nameserver addresses

---------
Step : 03
---------

- now in route53 hosted zone use create record 
- choose recordname whatever you want in my case it is "iam"
- in record type choose 'A record'
- in Value give public ip of ec2-instance
- keep routing policy to "Simple Routing"	

check your website after 10-15 minutes of the operation
